headline: US judge blocks ex-Palantir staffers from poaching workers for new AI firm
summary: A federal judge in Manhattan on Wednesday granted Palantir Technologies' bid to block a former vice president and senior engineer from soliciting ‌its employees to join the competing company they launched last year, Percepta AI.  The ruling ‌by U.S. District Judge Paul Oetken will be in place pending the outcome of Palantir's lawsuit filed in October claiming ​Percepta CEO Hirsh Jain and co-founder Radha Jain used Palantir's secret information to build a "copycat" AI software firm.  Oetken also barred Joanna Cohen, a former Palantir engineer now with Percepta, from breaching a confidentiality agreement she had signed with Palantir.
